      ],
      "phones": [
        "512-251-6995"
      ],
      "emails": [],
      "website": "https://ssvdp.org/",
      "description": "Central Texas St. Vincent de Paul (SVdP) coordinates local parish conferences that provide emergency financial assistance and basic needs to people in crisis across Austin/Travis County and surrounding counties. Typical help may include limited rent or utility assistance to prevent eviction or disconnection, help with medications, transportation, food, clothing, and referrals to other agencies. Assistance is generally provided through a ‘home visit’ or phone intake by volunteers who serve specific geographic areas. Veterans can be served like any other neighbor in need; being homeless may increase urgency but does not guarantee funding. To get help, the client must first be matched to the correct parish conference for their current sleeping/location address using the SVdP locator or by contacting the Council office.",
      "justification": "Client is a homeless veteran in Austin/Travis County needing emergency financial assistance. The Austin Diocesan Council oversees SVdP conferences that provide financial aid (rent, utilities, other emergency bills, transportation, food, clothing, etc.) to people in need across Central Texas and directs callers to the correct parish-based conference for their location. This is the best single entry point when the client’s exact address and parish boundaries are not yet known.",
      "referral_type": "external"
    },
    {
      "name": "St. Vincent de Paul – Locator via St. Mary Cathedral / Austin SVdP",
      "addresses": [
        "203 E. 10th St, Austin, TX 78701"
      ],
      "phones": [],
      "emails": [],
      "website": "https://austinsvdp.info",
      "description": "The Austin-area St. Vincent de Paul locator site helps neighbors find the specific SVdP conference that serves their address. After entering a full current address (or closest intersection/shelter address for people experiencing homelessness), the tool lists the parish conference name, phone number, and instructions for requesting assistance. Local conferences commonly help with emergency financial needs such as rent, utilities, limited other bills, food, and basic needs, subject to available funds and parish boundaries. Many conferences conduct an intake interview and may do a home or site visit before providing assistance.",
      "justification": "Case manager asked what St. Vincent de Paul offers in Austin for emergency financial assistance. The client’s exact sleeping address and parish boundary are unknown, so the SVdP locator is the appropriate way to identify the correct Austin/Travis County conference and its intake phone number for financial help.",
